Vtabs Component — `$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs`

Vertical tab list with typed elements. Each element has a type that determines its behavior and appearance.

Parameters:

|!Parameter |!Default |!Description |
|`elements` |`""` |TW filter returning element list |
|`type-fn` |`""` |TW filter that maps `<<element>>` to a type code (`sec`, `act`, `lnk`, `pop`, `sco`, `spa`) |
|`state` |auto |State tiddler prefix |
|`instid` |auto |Unique instance ID |
|`visible-types` |`"sec"` |Space-separated type codes always visible (not affected by section collapse) |
|`default-collapsed` |`"yes"` |Start with sections collapsed |
|`lnk-navigate` |`"yes"` |Navigate to element title on `lnk` click |

Element types:

|!Type |!Click behavior |!Visibility |!Use for |
|`sec` |Toggle section collapse |Always visible |Section headers, group dividers |
|`act` |Stores element in `<state>:last-click` |Follows section collapse |Action buttons, menu items |
|`lnk` |Navigates to element (tiddler title) |Follows section collapse |Links to other tiddlers |
|`pop` |No action (placeholder) |Follows section collapse |Informational items |
|`sco` |No action (subcomponent handles clicks) |Follows section collapse |Nested components (e.g., pills inside vtabs) |
|`spa` |No action |Follows section collapse |Visual spacers/separators |

The `type-fn` filter receives `<<element>>` and must return one type code. Use `then[]` chains:

```
[<element>prefix[section-]then[sec]]
  ~[<element>prefix[act-]then[act]]
  ~[<element>prefix[lnk-]then[lnk]]
  ~[<element>prefix[scomp-]then[sco]]
```

Slots (type-specific views):

|!Slot |!Variables |!Description |
|`view-sec` |`element` |Render section headers |
|`view-act` |`element` |Render action items |
|`view-lnk` |`element` |Render links |
|`view-pop` |`element` |Render popup items |
|`view-sco` |`element` |Render subcomponents |
|`view-spa` |`element` |Render spacers |
|`view` |`element`, `element-type` |Fallback for any type without a specific slot |

Each type-specific slot falls back to the generic `view` slot, which falls back to rendering the element value as plain text.

Section collapse:

- Clicking a `sec` element toggles visibility of its child elements (elements between this `sec` and the next `sec`)
- Each section collapses independently — toggling one section does not affect others
- `default-collapsed="yes"` means only `sec` elements (and other `visible-types`) show on load
- Elements before the first `sec` in the list are always visible
- Collapse state is stored as a list of toggled sections in the state tiddler

Interactive content in fills (stop-propagation):

- Vtabs uses an `$eventcatcher` on `.rrc-elem` rows — clicks anywhere on a row trigger the type handler (e.g., `lnk` navigates)
- To prevent this when fills contain buttons, popups, or other interactive elements, wrap them with `class="rrc-no-propagate"`
- Example: `<span class="rrc-no-propagate"><$button>...</$button></span>`
- The component catches clicks on `.rrc-no-propagate` elements and stops propagation before reaching the row handler

Reading last action:

When an `act` element is clicked, its value is stored in `<state>:last-click`:

```
Last action: <$text text={{$:/state/my/vtabs:last-click}}/>
```

